  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Help Us Raise Wetland Conservation by Prizing Kids</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Mucura Award for Wetland Conservation stimulates knowledge and recognizes commitment of rural children &amp; youth to the conservation of wetlands in provinces, each year. A first pilot focuses on the province of Sugamuxi (Boyaca, COL) which consists of 13 towns, but we are willing to gradually spread this over into more regions. It rewards positive actions on local rural wetlands made at an early age, aiming to raise awareness on securing its multiple services, especially on climate challenges.</narrative>
  </description>
